                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> While in the quiet times on a raid (awaiting pulls, doing CoH etc) regen is handy. Beats having to click off lich and then re-shrink, or having to get healed frequently.<br /><br />How important it is, depends largely on what you are doing tbh. Solo/group (frequent mobs) - nice to have, but not vital.<br /><br />Max Regen for items is 30 worn (yes, they will stack to this maximum limit).<br /><br />So, SoS = 50mana/33HP after worn regen (then add on your base regen to that).<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
