                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">1) Are regen items such as zlandicars heart worth it and do effects stack? (e.g. with an item with aura of battle on it)<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote">Are they worth it?  Yes and no.  Regen items really decrease in value as you level.  Once you get Vexing, regen is largely irrelevant.  Once you get SK (as someone said above), it really negates the need for regen items.  I've had a Zheart forever...I'm finding it less and less useful as I level.<br /><br />Do they stack?  Yes.  All innate regen items (i.e. they do not have a buff icon) stack up to the worn regen cap...which I think is 35 (don't quote me on that number though).<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">2) I "heard" a while back that wearing a haste item confirs the haste on the pet? Any truth in this?<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote">Categorically untrue.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">3) If there was any ONE must have item except a circlet of shadow, what should it be?<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote">I'd rank a pre-nerf CoS number one on my list.  After that, Affliction Efficiency and Affliction Haste.  Holgresh Elder Beads would be high on the list as well, but they are nearly impossible to find (and enormously expensive if you do find them).<br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
