                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> My thoughts .. for what htey are worth:<br /><br />1) Regen is usefull and stacks up to 30, I believe. I have the z-heart, however, not for the regen so much as the int. With 20 int on one item (and 15 on my bracelet of comprehension) I have a lot of freedom to get worthwhile items in other slots that have no int on them. There are some great +hp, or focus effect items out there that have low or no int on them. <br /><br />Gear questions, imho, can't be asked about any item per se, but have to be looked at holistically -- what OTHER gear do you have? What's your HP total? What's your mana pool? What's your total regen already? What focus effects do you have? Are you a raider, grouper, solo'er? What AA's do you have? What AA's do you plan to get?<br /><br />For me, my play style, and my other gear, a z-heart is a great item. For someone else it may well be the suck. <br /><br />2. Never heard that, doubt if it's true. If it is true, it's almost surely a bug.<br /><br />3. No, not even CoS. It's nice. I'd buy one if I saw it for sale. But it's not a "must have." A neked 65 necro with bone chips and peridots is a force to be reckoned with in any zone already. Gear makes you better, but being a necro is what makes you great.<br /><br />That said, focus items and clicky pet-buffs (ala ornate pants) are serious upgrades to your day-to-day life that should not be overlooked as part of your gear selection (see point 1). Also, don't sell FT items short. FT15, MC3, and SoS come together to make it HARD to use your mana. You will always have mana to nuke, tap, dot, twitch, sell on the street, whatever... and that's a good thing.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                     <td colspan="2" valign="bottom" align="left" height="20"><hr noshade size="2"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"></td></tr><td width="100%" nowrap>
