                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The people that say "I don't need a CoS" or "I do fine without one" fail to understand that a CoS isn't used for regular ol' exp in PoV or whatever. It's used for doing difficult things in places where having invis up quickly is important. Things like dungeons (yeh, most of the newer folks are like 'wtf is a dungeon?" and other spots where there are a lot of mobs up. Sure, you don't need one to grind out AAs sitting in some candyass pop plane all day.. but is that all you do? Are you just an AA machine? Where is the fun in that? Don't you ever try to push your skillset, refine it, test it, try to do things that are difficult, challenging, and fun? If so, usually doing these sorts of things involves getting past some extremely boring gauntlet of gay mobs first, in which case things like innate ITU and prenerf CoS are really handy. I dunno, maybe I and the others that feel a prenerf CoS is that valuable in their pack are just high on crack, but perhaps we just actually do more than simply sit and run around in circles all day in PoV too.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
